author: Nicole Acevedo
title: 'Illegal' party that violated stay-at-home order broken up by police
description: New Jersey Gov. Phil Murphy said the organizer of a house party in Ewing Township is facing charges after cramming 47 people in a small apartment during the coronavirus pandemic.
content:
Police in New Jersey broke up a house party in which 47 people crammed into a small apartment in violation of the state's stay-at-home order and social distancing guidelines, the state governor said. The organizer was charged.
